#     o 72 SLogP atom types are listed
#     o AtomTypes::SLogPAtomTypes.pm module is used to assign ALogP atom types using
#       an internal atom environment detection methodology. SMARTS strings are listed for
#       reference purposed and are not used by SLogPAtomTypes.pm module.
#        the AtomTypeSymbols are mapped to supplemental atom types or other atom types and
#        the MR values of mapped AtomTypeSymbols are used:
#     o SMARTS description [ Copied from Ref 89 ]
#         o 'A' and 'a' are used to represent any non-hydrogen aliphatic and aromatic element
#         o '[#X]' is used to specify any non-hydrogen
#           aromaticity may be specified by including the appropriate 'A' or 'a'
#         o '[#N]' specifies any element in the subset of elements O
#           subject to the same aromaticity control.
#           Other elements may be specified using '[# atomic number]'

column2: such that '[a#7]' indicates an aromatic Nitrogen

column1: #           Absence of a specific bond symbol implies a single or aromatic bond.
#         o The number of attached hydrogens is specified using H
#           Carbon in methane. Charge is indicated with + and - such that '[#7+*]' indicates a
#         o 'X' without '#' is used to specify the total number of bonds

column2: so '[CX4]' would match the Carbon in methane as well as the quaternary

column1: #           Carbon of a tert-butyl group. All other notation follows that of the original SMARTS.
#     o Number of atom type symbols for:

column2: carbon supplemental not matching any basic C type
hydrogen supplemental not matching any basic H type
nitrogen supplemental not matching any basic N type
oxygen supplemental not matching any basic O type
